      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates <2% change in QoI between successive refinements; Richardson extrapolation applied to estimate discretization error.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh convergence study was performed at element sizes 1.0 mm, 0.5 mm, and 0.35 mm. Change in peak von Mises stress between 0.5 mm and 0.35 mm was 1.4%. Richardson extrapolation yielded a grid convergence index of 0.8% on construct stiffness. Achieved level exceeds required level."
