      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model selection (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) justified by coupon data; contact formulation validated against known analytical solutions.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening was selected for Ti-6Al-4V based on tensile coupon data from the same material lot. Tangent modulus was fit to the post-yield region (E_t = 2.1 GPa). Augmented Lagrange contact between screw and block was verified against a Hertzian contact benchmark. Model form uncertainty was quantified using a ±5% perturbation on E_t, yielding a 1.2% change in stiffness QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing; geometry from calibrated CMM measurements; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114.2 ± 2.3 GPa) and yield strength (896 ± 18 MPa) were measured from five tensile coupons from the same Ti-6Al-4V bar stock. Screw geometry was digitised using a Zeiss CMM with 2 µm resolution. Input uncertainty was propagated via a 200-sample Monte Carlo analysis, contributing ±2.8% to stiffness QoI uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens from production-representative lots; dimensional inspection confirms geometry within drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production-representative lots. Dimensional inspection of five randomly selected screws confirmed all critical dimensions within ±0.05 mm of nominal. UHMWPE blocks were machined to ASTM F1717 geometry and verified by CMM."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Testing performed under at least two distinct loading rates or configurations to characterise test condition sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "All testing was performed at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717. No variation in loading rate or fixture configuration was explored. This limits the ability to characterise test condition sensitivity and results in achieved level (2) below required level (3). This known gap is accepted given the standardised nature of F1717 and the low sensitivity of quasi-static stiffness to loading rate in this regime."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions, fixture geometry, and material inputs demonstrably equivalent to experimental conditions; any differences quantified.",
      "rationale": "FEA fixture geometry was imported directly from CAD drawings of the ASTM F1717 test apparatus. Actuator load application point and constraint locations were matched to within 0.1 mm. Block material (UHMWPE, E = 0.93 GPa) was assigned from supplier data sheet values confirmed by lab compressive testing. Residual differences between FEA and experimental setup were assessed as contributing <0.5% to QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (percent difference and E/uval) computed for all three QoIs; acceptance thresholds pre-registered in study protocol.",
      "rationale": "Percent difference and E/uval were computed for stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement. All three QoIs satisfied percent difference <10% and E/uval <1.96. Acceptance thresholds were pre-registered in the study protocol prior to unblinding of experimental results."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
