      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly correspond to clinical performance metrics and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield force are the primary mechanical performance metrics cited in FDA guidance for spinal pedicle screw systems. Force at 40 mm displacement characterises post-yield energy absorption relevant to fatigue life prediction. All three QoIs are directly traceable to the COU decision question."
